The paper discusses a method for integrating a domain specific language (DSL) into an algorithmic differentiation (AD) tool, which is a software engineering problem (cs.SE). The approach involves operator overloading, which is a programming language concept (cs.PL). The paper also discusses performance optimization, which is a machine learning concept (cs.LG) and involves reducing memory requirements, which is a distributed, parallel, and cluster computing concept (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the consistency of derivatives with the computation of the software, which is a scientific computing concept (cs.SC).
